questions.text: Your resume highlights your experience building a reporting tool for DTU, replacing an existing system with a 94% efficiency gain. Can you walk me through the product management aspects of that project, including defining the problem, gathering requirements, prioritizing features, and measuring success?

You analyzed 52 pitches from Shark Tank India, identifying a 55% conversion rate for women-led businesses.  As a product manager, how would you use this data to inform product strategy and drive inclusivity within a product or service?

Your Pizza Sales Metrics project involved analyzing 50,000 records and creating a Power BI dashboard with 25+ KPIs. Describe your process for identifying key performance indicators (KPIs) and how you ensured the data visualizations were effective and actionable for stakeholders.

You mention leading your basketball team to first place.  Transferring this leadership experience to a product management context, how would you motivate and manage a cross-functional team to achieve ambitious product goals, especially when faced with challenges or setbacks?

Given your proficiency in various programming languages (Python, JavaScript, SQL) and data analysis tools (Power BI, MySQL), how would you leverage these technical skills to make data-driven decisions and inform product development during the product lifecycle?
